This paper is primarily focused on robotics planning, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the use of classical AI planning techniques, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of search algorithms and heuristics to find plans suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the manipulation of objects, which could potentially fall under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
